        "Club career": "Born in Etterbeek, Belgium, Bidaoui has played club football in Belgium for Westerlo, Roeselare and Lierse. In the summer of 2013, Bidaoui signed a contract with Italian team Parma. He joined Crotone on loan for the 2013–14 season.On 11 July 2016 Bidaoui was signed by Avellino in a 2-year contract, plus option of further season.On 20 August 2018, he joined Serie B club Spezia.On 14 January 2021 he signed with Ascoli.On 31 January 2023, Bidaoui moved to Frosinone on a 1.5-year contract.",
